ling, decision speed, or teamwork.\n**Remaining uncertainty**: How B\u2019s pretentiousness and tone issues manifest in real flight\u2011deck interactions; concrete evidence of B\u2019s overall reliability and decision\u2011making speed; and any additional positive data on A\u2019s stress handling, C\u2019s communication effectiveness, or D\u2019s leadership in crew settings.\n**What would change my vote**: Strong, concrete evidence that B\u2019s teamwork issues are minor or can be mitigated, or compelling positive evidence that another candidate matches B\u2019s technical and stress\u2011handling strengths while demonstrating superior crew\u2011interaction and communication abilities (e.g., A handling stress well, or C showing effective crew communication).\nMETADATA_JSON:\n{\"agent\": \"agent_2\", \"vote\": \"Candidate B\"}", "thoughts": "We need to produce public message and metadata. As agent_2, we have the same info as before plus new info about Candidate A from Agent1: unfriendly, not good at taking criticism, unorganized, eats unhealthily, no stress handling info. Also we have all other candidate info. We need to consider if any new info changes our vote. Previously we favored B. The new info about A further weakens A. No new info about others. So likely still B. But we must also consider uncertainties: B's teamwork issues. Could any other candidate be better? C has good crew concern, quick decisions, calm, but communication difficulty and egocentric, not willing to further education. D has strong problem solving, responsibility, but moody, loner, weak leadership. B still seems best. So we keep vote B, with confidence maybe 70% as before. Provide summary.\n\nWe must include evidence from others: other agents also favor B. Provide major alternatives: A, C, D with their strengths/weaknesses. Main tradeoff: B's interpersonal issues vs others' deficits. Remaining uncertainty: B's teamwork impact, lack of data on decision speed, etc. What would change vote: eviden